23\\\" height=\\\"307\\\" /></p>\\r\\n<h3>Anthony Morisi</h3>\\r\\n<ul\n    style=\\\"margin-left: 350px;\\\">\\r\\n<li>Age: 31</li>\\r\\n<li>Experience:</li>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>5\n    Years of CrossFit</li>\\r\\n<li>1 Year of Coaching</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n<li>Certifications:</li>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>CrossFit\n    Level 1 (2012)</li>\\r\\n<li>USAW Level 1 (2012)</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n<p>In\n    the Spring of 2008, I started my career as a firefighter. I was looking for a\n    fitness program that would prepare me, physically and mentally, for the rigors\n    of my new career. This was when I found CrossFit. In CrossFit, I found a training\n    program and methodology that challenged me constantly and developed the functional\n    fitness that I needed to take on my new career as well as everything that else\n    life had in store for me. I had found a new passion that was all about, hard work,\n    mental toughness and community. My passion for CrossFit has changed my life. &nbsp;Now,\n    as a coach, I love seeing the change in others as we grow our community of fit,\n    accountable, and confident human beings.</p>\"\n','2013-11-29 22:32:53'),(20,'Cms::Page',5,'---\nblocks_attributes:\n- :identifier: content\n  :content: \"<h1 id=\\\"location\\\">Location</h1>\\r\\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\\r\\n<div style=\\\"display:\n    table;\\\">\\r\\n<div style=\\\"font-size: 11px; padding-left: 60px; display: table-cell;\\\"><img\n    id=\\\"map\\\" src=\\\"../../../../../system/cms/files/files/000/000/005/original/cfb.png\\\"\n    alt=\\\"map\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"300\\\" /></div>\\r\\n<div style=\\\"vertical-align:\n    middle; font-size: 18pt; text-align: center; display: table-cell; padding-left:\n    20px;\\\">\\r\\n<div>2914 Sylvan Ave <br />Baltimore, MD 21214</div>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\\r\\n<h1\n    id=\\\"crossfit\\\">What is Crossfit?</h1>\\r\\n<p>CrossFit is defined as &ldquo;constantly\n    varied, functional movements, performed at high intensity&rdquo;. What does this\n    mean? <strong>Functional Movements</strong> are those movements that you perform\n    every day. They are the natural, effective, and efficient movements that are used\n    to move your body as well as other objects. They allow us to move large loads\n    over long distances and to do so quickly. <strong>Intensity</strong> is synonymous\n    with power which is a measurement of how much, how many, how far, and how fast\n    we perform these functional movements. Intensity is relative to each individual\n    and the idea is to maximize each individual&rsquo;s level of intensity. <strong>Constantly\n    Varied</strong> means to take these functional movements and perform them in as\n    many different combinations and variations as possible.</p>\\r\\n<p>CrossFit, in\n    practice, is a Strength and Conditioning Program that is &ldquo;broad, general,\n    and inclusive&rdquo;, developing the functional fitness necessary to be ready\n    for the unknown. It aims to prepare you for whatever task life has in store for\n    you and in the same sense can be used by each individual to further their specific\n    goals. CrossFit combines Power Lifting, Olympic Weightlifting, Gymnastics, Kettlebell\n    Training, Running, Rowing, Jumping Rope, Mobility, and more to develop and maximize\n    these <strong>10 General Physical Skills</strong>:</p>\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n<li>Cardiovascular/Respiratory\n    Endurance</li>\\r\\n<li>Stamina</li>\\r\\n<li>Strength</li>\\r\\n<li>Flexibility</li>\\r\\n<li>Power</li>\\r\\n<li>Speed</li>\\r\\n<li>Coordination</li>\\r\\n<li>Agility</li>\\r\\n<li>Balance</li>\\r\\n<li>Accuracy</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n<p>CrossFit\n    is for people from all walks of life; from professional athletes to senior citizens\n    to people with disabilities. Every workout can be scaled to fit the fitness level\n    of the individual so that everyone is performing at the threshold of their own\n    personal limitations. CrossFit is more than a fitness program. CrossFit is an\n    international community of people that challenge themselves and encourage others\n    to challenge themselves to be better athletes and better people. CrossFit develops\n    the physical and mental toughness and confidence to take on any and all of life&rsquo;s\n    challenges.</p>\\r\\n<blockquote>\\r\\n<p>&ldquo;World-Class Fitness in 100 Words:<br\n    /> Eat meat and vegetables, nuts and seeds, some fruit, little starch and no sugar.\n    Keep intake to levels that will support exercise but not body fat. Practice and\n    train major lifts: Deadlift, clean, squat, presses, C&amp;J, and snatch. Similarly,\n    master the basics of gymnastics: pull-ups, dips, rope climb, push-ups, sit-ups,\n    presses to handstand, pirouettes, flips, splits, and holds. Bike, run, swim, row,\n    etc, hard and fast. Five or six days per week mix these elements in as many combinations\n    and patterns as creativity will allow. Routine is the enemy. Keep workouts short\n    and intense. Regularly learn and play new sports.&rdquo;<br /><br /> <span style=\\\"float:\n    right;\\\">~ Greg Glassman (Owner and Founder of CrossFit)</span></p>\\r\\n</blockquote>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\\r\\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\\r\\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\\r\\n<h1\n    id=\\\"coaches\\\">Coaches</h1>\\r\\n<p><img style=\\\"float: right;\\\" src=\\\"../../../../../system/cms/files/files/000/000/003/original/dom.png\\\"\n    alt=\\\"Dom\\\" width=\\\"325\\\" height=\\\"312\\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div>\\r\\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\\r\\n<h3>Dominic\n    Morisi</h3>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>Age: 27</li>\\r\\n<li>Experience:</li>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>5\n    Years of CrossFit</li>\\r\\n<li>5 Years of Coaching</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n<li>Certifications:</li>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>NFPT\n    (2009)</li>\\r\\n<li>CrossFit Level1(2011)</li>\\r\\n<li>USAW Level1 (2012)</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n<p>My\n    name is Dominic Morisi, and I was born and